Parliament, Monday, 5 October 2020 – The Portfolio Committee on Tourism,
	(National Assembly), will tomorrow receive a briefing from the Department of Tourism on its first quarter performance report for the 2020/21 financial year. Furthermore, the committee will consider the draft Committee Report for the third and fourth quarters performance for the 2019/20 financial year.
	
	Details of the virtual meeting are as follows:
	Date : Tuesday, 6 October 2020
	Time: 09:00 – 12:00
	
	Members of the media who would like to be part of the meeting to observe may forward their contact details to Mr Mlindi Mpindi on +27 81 716 7329 for inclusion in the Parliament Communications Service WhatsApp group, where login details will be shared
	
	Members of the public may get involved and follow committee sittings live on Parliament TV (DStv Channel 408), via live stream on Parliament YouTube channel and Twitter page on the links below. You may subscribe to the Parliament YouTube channel to receive instant notification of live feeds.
	
	Twitter: https://twitter.com/ParliamentofRSA
	Facebook: https://facebook.com/ParliamentofRSA
	YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/ParliamentofRSA
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON TOURISM, MR SUPRA MAHUMAPELO.
	
	For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairpersons, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer:
